io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.target

Interface ISyncTargetDataFactory


  • public interface ISyncTargetDataFactory
    Factory to create target specific data instances to write meta data to.

    Meta data is structured into various classes (interfaces). Target specific instances are used to store these meta data. Implementors of this factory are delivering such instances, related to the DAM target.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      BaseSyncAsset createSyncBinaryAsset()

    • Method Detail

      • createSyncBinaryAsset

        BaseSyncAsset createSyncBinaryAsset()
        Factory function to create a new instance representing target's data structure for a Binary Assets.

        The newly created instance MUST NOT be stored automatically on the sync target prior to returning it. For storing this instance, it will be passed to this sync target via ISyncTarget.importNewTargetAssets(BaseSyncAsset[]).

        Returns:
        must return a fresh instance for every call and must not ever return null.
        See Also:
        BaseSyncAsset

      • createSyncCompoundAsset

        BaseSyncAsset createSyncCompoundAsset()

        Returns:
        must return a fresh instance for every call and must not ever return null.
        See Also:
        BaseSyncAsset

      • createSyncLicenseTerm

        ISyncLicenseTerm createSyncLicenseTerm()
        Factory function to create a new instance representing target's lincense terms data structure.

        The newly created instance SHOULD NOT be stored automatically on the sync target prior to returning it. For storing this instance, it will be attached to an asset via BaseSyncAsset.setLicenseTerms(ISyncLicenseTerm[]) and thus passed to this sync target via one of ISyncTarget.importNewTargetAssets(BaseSyncAsset[]), ISyncTarget.importNewTargetCompoundAssets(BaseSyncAsset[]), ISyncTarget.updateTargetAssets(BaseSyncAsset[]), ISyncTarget.updateTargetCompoundAssets(BaseSyncAsset[])

        Returns:
        must return a fresh instance for every call and must not ever return null.
